@mattpocockuk @fastifyjs But for internals, you probably don't want your imports messing them up.

Even better would be to slap a Zod parser onto your input boundary before feeding the parsed data to your internals.

And the types can be derived from that parser, win-win.

@mattpocockuk Types for internals &amp; unexposed APIs

Interface for extensible, exposed APIs.

Things like configuration or context that gets passed down, in and out of the export boundary makes a great use-case for interfaces (see @fastifyjs' instance/req/res), because of declaration merging.

